Package task6.money

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    A_Currency
    Defines the shared elements of a currency denomination that can represent any unit of coin or bill; e.g., dime, nickel, single, five.
    A_CurrencyCoin
    Defines the shared elements of a currency denomination that can represent any unit of coin; e.g., dime, nickel.
    A_CurrencyPaper
    Defines the shared elements of a currency denomination that can represent any unit of bill; e.g., single, five.
    CurrencyCoinCent_10
    Defines a currency unit representing a 10-cent coin.
    CurrencyCoinCent_25
    Defines a currency unit representing a 25-cent coin.
    CurrencyCoinCent_5
    Defines a currency unit representing a five-cent coin.
    CurrencyCoinDollar_1
    Defines a currency unit representing a dollar coin.
    CurrencyManager
    Defines a manager for manipulating currency.
    CurrencyPaperDollar_1
    Defines a currency unit representing a dollar bill.
    CurrencyPaperDollar_10
    Defines a currency unit representing a 10-dollar bill.
    CurrencyPaperDollar_2
    Defines a currency unit representing a two-dollar bill.
    CurrencyPaperDollar_5
    Defines a currency unit representing a five-dollar bill.
    Money
    Defines a unit for maintaining and manipulating monetary values in dollars and cents.
